Title: Topologically Nontrivial Sectors of Maxwell Field Theory on Riemann

SurfacesAuthors: Franco Ferrari

Comments: 8 pages, TeX + harvmac, to appear in Lett. Math. Phys

Journal-ref: Lett.Math.Phys. 41 (1997) 371-378

In this paper the Maxwell field theory is considered on a closed andorientable Riemann surface of genus $h>1$. The solutions of the Maxwellequations corresponding to nontrivial values of the first Chern class areexplicitly constructed for any metric in terms of the prime form.